9 STATE BOARD OF EDUCATION/OFFICE OF THE SUPERINTENDENT
10 Sec. 351. (1) The department may use the appropriations from
11 the state board of education, per diem payments in part 1 for per
12 diem payments to the state board members for meetings at which a
13 quorum is present or for performing official business authorized by
14 the state board. The per diem payments are set at the following
15 rates:
16 (a) State board of education - president - $110.00 per day.
17 (b) State board of education - member other than president -
18 $100.00 per day.
19 (2) The department shall not pay a state board of education
20 member a per diem for more than 30 days per year.
